page.title: 12A Cannington girl's day.
page.content: At 7.15am I get up and dress and go downstairs to make my sandwiches for school. These usually consists of bread, butter and a filling. Then I make my breakfast which is usually a cereal called Cornflakes which I eat with milk and usually quite a lot of sugar. After my breakfast I watch the television. In the morning there is a programme called "Good Morning Britain" which is on a channel called I.T.V . Then at 8.00am I wash the dishes. At 8.30am I make my way to school. On the way I call for Julie, one of my friends. School starts at 9.00am. At 3.10pm we go home. I get home at 3.30pm and play with some of my friends. I go in at 4.40pm for tea. After tea I watch television,have a bath and go to bed at 9.15pm to read.
